     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "AIMessage(content=[{'type': 'text', 'text': 'At its simplest, **LangChain is a software framework designed to make it easier to build applications powered by Large Language Models (LLMs)** like GPT-4 (OpenAI), Claude (Anthropic), or Llama (Meta).\\n\\nIf an LLM is like the \"brain,\" LangChain is the \"nervous system\" that connects that brain to the rest of the world.\\n\\n### Why do we need LangChain?\\nBy themselves, LLMs have limitations:\\n* **Static Knowledge:** They only know what they were trained on (the \"cutoff date\" problem).\\n* **No Action:** They cannot easily browse the live web, access your private files, or perform actions (like sending an email).\\n* **Context Limits:** They can only \"read\" a certain amount of text at one time.\\n\\nLangChain provides a set of tools to bridge these gaps.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Core Concepts of LangChain\\nTo understand how LangChain works, think of these four building blocks:\\n\\n#### 1. Models (LLM Wrappers)\\nLangChain provides a standard interface for almost any LLM. This means you can swap from using OpenAI’s GPT-4 to Google’s Gemini or an open-source model like Llama 3 with just one line of code, without rewriting your whole application.\\n\\n#### 2. Prompts (Templates)\\nInstead of hard-coding prompts, LangChain allows you to create \"Prompt Templates.\" You can define a structure (e.g., \"Act as a helpful assistant for [User Role]\") and then dynamically inject variables (like the user\\'s name or current date) into that template.\\n\\n#### 3. Chains\\nThis is where the name comes from. Usually, a task isn\\'t just one prompt. You might need to:\\n1. Search a database for documents.\\n2. Summarize those documents.\\n3. Translate the summary into another language.\\nLangChain allows you to \"chain\" these steps together so the output of one becomes the input for the next.\\n\\n#### 4. Retrieval (RAG - Retrieval Augmented Generation)\\nThis is the most popular use case. If you want an AI to answer questions about your private company data (PDFs, SQL databases, or Notion pages), LangChain helps you:\\n* Break the documents into small chunks.\\n* Store them in a \"Vector Database.\"\\n* Search for the relevant chunks when a user asks a question.\\n* Feed only those specific chunks to the LLM to get an accurate, context-aware answer.\\n\\n#### 5. Agents\\nAgents are the \"advanced\" part of LangChain. Instead of just giving the LLM a task, you give the LLM a **toolkit** (like a calculator, a Google Search tool, or a database query tool). The LLM then decides *which* tool to use and *when* to use it to solve a complex problem.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### A Simple Analogy\\nImagine you are hiring a brilliant genius (the LLM) to do research for you:\\n* **Without LangChain:** You hand them a book and tell them to write a report. But if they don\\'t know something, they can\\'t leave the room to find a computer.\\n* **With LangChain:** You give the genius a **phone** (search tool), a **library card** (database access), and a **step-by-step checklist** (chains). They are now much more capable because you’ve given them a way to interact with tools and information outside of their own memory.\\n\\n### Is LangChain for you?\\n* **If you are a beginner** and just want to ask ChatGPT a question, you don\\'t need LangChain.\\n* **If you are a developer** who wants to build a chatbot that talks to your private data, performs tasks, or links multiple AI steps together, LangChain is the industry standard framework to get that done quickly.\\n\\n**Language Support:** LangChain is primarily available in **Python** and **JavaScript (TypeScript)**.', 'extras': {'signature': 'EjQKMgERTTIPrfk324W7dlQgNjNcyVZhjSazOOcPWrHGFUSMxkrlZoplM09eT3zmm0/9PKNj'}}], additional_kwargs={}, response_metadata={'finish_reason': 'STOP', 'model_name': 'gemini-3.1-flash-lite', 'safety_ratings': [], 'model_provider': 'google_genai'}, id='lc_run--019f8acf-24f7-78b1-bf6b-eeca0a4850d2-0', tool_calls=[], invalid_tool_calls=[], usage_metadata={'input_tokens': 5, 'output_tokens': 840, 'total_tokens': 845, 'input_token_details': {'cache_read': 0}})"
      ]
     },
